{"cursor":"4591","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nIn physiology, 'perfusion' is the process of delivery of blood to a capillary\nbed in the biological tissue. The word is derived from the French verb\n\"perfuser\" meaning to \"pour over or through.\"\n\nTests of adequate perfusion are a part of the patient assessment process\nperformed by medical or emergency personnel. The most common methods include\nevaluating skin color, temperature, condition and capillary refill.\n","linknr":543,"url":"Perfusion","recorded":1362538668,"links":29,"instances":["medicine","99mtc_sestamibi"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Respiratory physiology","Cardiovascular physiology","Underwater diving physiology"],"headings":["Overperfusion and underperfusion","Discovery","Measurement","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Lindbergh_perfusion_pump_in_Putnam_Gallery%2C_2009-11-24.jpg/170px-Lindbergh_perfusion_pump_in_Putnam_Gallery%2C_2009-11-24.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg/8px-Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Helmet_logo_for_Underwater_Diving_portal.png/20px-Helmet_logo_for_Underwater_Diving_portal.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/SpongeDiver.jpg/100px-SpongeDiver.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["technetium","99mtc_sestamibi"],["bolus","medicine"]],"members":["bolus","technetium"],"related":["Physiology","Blood","Capillary","Biological_tissue","Medical","Hypoperfusion","Heart","Thermoregulation","Oxygen","Dissipation","Sweating","Thermal_dissipation","